		</div><div class="link">
			<a href="/recipe/26/Simple-Tiramisu">Simple Tiramisu</a>
		</div>
	
</div>
	For larger groups or potlucks, I double the portions and prepare exactly as above until the meat mixture is done cooking. Instead of transfering the meat to a baking pan, I put the potatoes into the pot to cover the meat mixture. (If I know that there will be many carb dishes at the meal, then I won't double the potato portion.) After fluffing the potatoes, I bake the whole pot for 30 minutes at 400&#176;F.<?}?></span><br />
<br />
<b>Shepherd's Pie</b> (serves <span itemprop="yield">four to six</span>)<br />
Mashed potatoes<br />
<table><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1-1/2 lb. (700 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">russet potatoes</span></span></td><td>boil until tender (15 min.)</td><td rowspan=3 class="vertical">mash</td><td rowspan=3 class="vertical">season to taste</td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1/2 cup (120 mL)</span> <span itemprop="name">water reserved from boiling potatoes</span></span></td><td rowspan=2 class="righthide"></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 Tbs. (14 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">unsalted butter</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="name">salt</span></span></td><td rowspan=2 colspan=2 class="righthide"></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">ground</span> <span itemprop="name">white pepper</span></span></td></tr></table><br />
Shepherd's pie<br />
<table><tr><td colspan=11 align=center>Preheat oven to 400&#176;F (204&#176;C)</td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">3 Tbs. (45 mL)</span> <span itemprop="name">vegetable oil</span></span></td><td>heat</td><td rowspan=4 class="vertical">med-low until tender</td><td rowspan=5 class="vertical">cook until meat is no longer pink</td><td rowspan=6 class="vertical">mix and cook</td><td rowspan=10 class="vertical">stir in and cook until liquid thickens</td><td rowspan=12 class="vertical">season to taste</td><td rowspan=13 class="vertical">cover with potatoes and fluff with fork</td><td rowspan=14 class="vertical">drop butter pieces on top</td><td rowspan=15 class="vertical">cover with paprika</td><td rowspan=15 class="vertical">bake 400&#176;F (205&#176;C) 30 min.</td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 medium (110 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">onion</span></span></td><td rowspan=3>dice</td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 medium (61 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">carrot</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 medium (40 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">celery stalk</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 pound (450 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">ground lamb</span></span></td><td colspan=2 class="righthide"></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 Tbs. (8 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">all-purpose flour</span></span></td><td colspan=3 class="righthide"></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 tsp. (1.2 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">dried rosemary</span></span></td><td rowspan=4 colspan=3 class="righthide"></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 tsp. (1 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">dried thyme</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 pinch</span> <span itemprop="name">ground nutmeg</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1 cup (235 mL)</span> <span itemprop="name">beef broth</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="name">salt</span></span></td><td rowspan=2 colspan=4 class="righthide"></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">ground</span> <span itemprop="name">black pepper</span></span></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">1-3/4 lb. (800 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">mashed potatoes</span></span></td><td colspan=5 class="righthide"></td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="amount">2 Tbs. (28 g)</span> <span itemprop="name">butter</span></span></td><td colspan=7>cut up into small pieces</td></tr><tr><td><span itemprop="ingredient" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/RecipeIngredient"><span itemprop="name">paprika</span></span></td><td colspan=7 class="righthide"></td></tr></table><br />
