					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On November 30, 2005 at 09:16 PM, Michael Chu said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Re: Shepherd's Pie</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Sandra wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>Does a Shepherd's pie freeze okay?  I have a lot of family coming for Christmas and I want to be prepared ahead with lots of comfy foods in the freezer!</div></div><br />
In my experience, shepherd's pie freezes just fine. Simply freeze it after it's been assembled (before baking) and when it's time to serve, just bake until the edges are bubbly.</div>
