					<div class="commentheading">On June 01, 2006 at 07:44 AM, an anonymous reader said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Since the potatoes are already mashed and warm, and the meat and vegetable portion of the dish are already fully cooked, and still hot from the range top, what do you lose by not simply broiling the dish for a few minutes, instead of a 400 oven for thirty minutes? It seems to me that you could save some time doing that, as well as perhaps saving some moisture in the lower strata of potatoes by not exposing it to the heat for so long.<br />
