					<div class="commentheading">On September 08, 2010 at 11:38 PM, sarahschmara (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Shepheard's pie!</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I use a couple spoons of beefy bovril in my "gravy" and, instead of making a whole pan at once, I portion them out into 1/2 pint canning jars (after much success with chicken pot-pies adapted from <a href='http://www.ourbestbites.com/2009/09/single-serving-pie-in-jar.html'>http://www.ourbestbites.com/2009/09/single-serving-pie-in-jar.html</a> protip: don't line the jars with pastry or the filling to crust ratio will be off) so there's at least a dozen easy dinners waiting patiently for me in the freezer. Is it time consuming? Sure! but it beats anything you can buy in the store hands down.[/url]</div>
