					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On March 03, 2012 at 12:58 AM, Ronald haeberle (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Shephard's-Cottage pie</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Firstly, Shepard's pie is made with lamb, not beef as its name implies. Cottage pie, is made from beef.  Therefore, the two names are not synonymous. <br />
<br />
In addition, a third meat pie, humble pie is made from the vital organs such as kidney, stomach, heart, etc. A pie made by the poor folks. The implication is that they could not afford the more desirable parts of these animals. They were left with the innards.<br />
<br />
A shepherd watches over lamb, not cattle, thus the name shepherd's pie.</div>
					<hr size="1" noshade />
				
